.TH MEETING\-RECORDER 1 "July 2026" "meeting-recorder 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
meeting\-recorder \- detect online meetings and record screen, microphone and system audio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B meeting\-recorder
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ \-v | \-\-verbose ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B meeting\-recorder
runs in the background and detects when a known communication application
(Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, Discord, Slack, Webex or a browser) starts
using the microphone. Instead of recording automatically it shows a desktop
notification asking permission. On confirmation it records the screen, the
microphone and optionally system audio, stopping automatically when the call
ends. Recordings are saved as
.IR <App>_<YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS>.mkv .
.PP
While recording, a tray icon provides a live timer plus pause, resume and stop.
Pausing excludes the paused time from the saved file.
.PP
This release captures the screen through X11
.RB ( x11grab )
and does not support Wayland sessions.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Print the background service state, the currently active audio capture streams,
and whether any matches a known meeting application.
.TP
.B start
Start the background service.
.TP
.B stop
Stop the background service, suspending meeting detection.
.TP
.B restart
Restart the background service, applying configuration changes.
.TP
.B logs
Follow the service log.
.TP
.B settings
Open the graphical settings window.
.TP
.B run
Start the detector daemon in the foreground. This is what the systemd user
service runs. Default when no command is given.
.TP
.B record
Start recording immediately and continue until interrupted with Ctrl\-C.
.TP
.B config
Create the user configuration file if missing and print its path.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable debug logging, including the exact ffmpeg command lines.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/meeting-recorder/config.json
User configuration. Overrides the shipped defaults. See
.B CONFIGURATION
below.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/meeting_recorder/default_config.json
Shipped default configuration.
.TP
.I ~/Videos/MeetingRecorder/
Default output directory for recordings.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Notable keys in the user configuration file:
.TP
.B output_dir
Directory for saved recordings.
.TP
.B capture_mode
.BR fullscreen ", " window " (focused window) or " area " (fixed rectangle)."
.TP
.B normalize_voice
Normalize the microphone and system audio to the same loudness so both voices
are at a comparable level. Enabled by default.
.TP
.B mic_volume ", " system_volume
Fine trim applied after normalization; 1.0 keeps both equal.
.TP
.B noise_cancellation
Filter background noise from the microphone.
.TP
.B auto_record
Skip the permission prompt and record automatically.
.TP
.B allowlist
Rules of the form
.RI { \(dqmatch\(dq : \(dqzoom\(dq , \(dqapp\(dq : \(dqZoom\(dq }
matched against the application using the microphone.
.SH SERVICE
The background service is a systemd
.I user
unit, not a system unit: it needs the caller's X display for screen capture,
PulseAudio session for audio, and D-Bus session for notifications and the tray
icon. The
.BR start ", " stop ", " restart " and " logs
commands wrap the equivalent
.B systemctl \-\-user
calls:
.PP
.nf
.RS
systemctl \-\-user status meeting\-recorder
systemctl \-\-user restart meeting\-recorder
journalctl \-\-user \-u meeting\-recorder \-f
.RE
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and non\-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ffmpeg (1),
.BR pactl (1)
.PP
Full documentation:
.UR https://github.com/ssKazal/meeting-recorder
